First Lady Michelle Obama sends a message of warm greetings to the United States-China Consultation on People-to-People Exchange (CPE) in Beijing, China. She thanks President Xi Jinping, Vice Premier Liu Yandong, and the Chinese delegation for hosting the US delegation. She also expresses gratitude to President Xi, Madame Peng, and the Chinese people for their hospitality during her recent visit to China. She highlights the importance of strengthening the bonds between the US and China and mentions various initiatives that have been collaborated on, such as encouraging women to pursue careers in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics, fostering educational opportunities through the Fulbright program, promoting youth development through the NBA Yao School, and forging relationships in sports between the US and China. The First Lady commends the participants for their role in building the relationship between the two nations and wishes them success in their efforts.